ta-toy-ioy-21-nea |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 31 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 21 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 |last=Newsroom |date=2020-03-05 |website=CNN.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114331/https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 14 \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1! |website=www.newsit.gr |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307063741/https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |archive-date=7 March 2020 }}</ref> Health and state authorities issued precautionary guidelines and recommendations, while measures up to that point were taken locally and included the closure of schools and the suspension of cultural events in the affected areas (particularly [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]]).<ref name=\":0\" /> The first confirmed death from COVID-19 in Greece was a 66-year-old man, who died on 12 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man/ |title=Greece reports first coronavirus death, 66-year-old man |date=12 March 2020 |website=straitstimes.com |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314014704/https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBy 15 April, there were 2192 confirmed cases in Greece, 102 deaths and 269 recoveries.<ref name=\"greececases\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.moh.gov.gr/articles/ministry/grafeio-typoy/press-releases/7083-enhmerwsh-diapisteymenwn-syntaktwn-ygeias-apo-ton-yfypoyrgo-politikhs-prostasias-kai-diaxeirishs-krisewn-niko-xardalia-kai-ton-ekproswpo-toy-ypoyrgeioy-ygeias-gia-to-neo-koronoio-kathhghth-swthrh-tsiodra-15-4-2020|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf \u03a7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc, \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03b7\u03c4\u03ae \u03a3\u03c9\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b7 \u03a4\u03c3\u03b9\u03cc\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1 (15/4/2020)|last=|first=|date=2020-04-15|website=Ministry of Health|language=el|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> The Greek [[National Public Health Organization (Greece)|National Public Health Organization]] (NPHO), in collaboration with local authorities and doctors, is tracking and testing everyone who came in close contact with the patients.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0388\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 |website=www.onmed.gr |language=el |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114330/https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561722/koronoios-deka-ta-kroysmata-stin-ellada |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0394\u03ad\u03ba\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 |website=antenna.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114327/https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561722/koronoios-deka-ta-kroysmata-stin-ellada |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> By March 10, with 89 confirmed cases and no deaths in the country, the government decided to suspend the operation of educational institutions of all levels nationwide and then, on 13 March, to close down all cafes, bars, museums, shopping centres, sports facilities and restaurants in the country.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/news/44308-10-03-20-prosorini-apagorefsi-tis-ekpaideftikis-leitourgias-olon-ton-ekpaideftikon-domon |title=\u03a5\u03a0\u039f\u03a5\u03a1\u0393\u0395\u0399\u039f \u03a0\u0391\u0399\u0394\u0395\u0399\u0391\u03a3 & \u0398\u03a1\u0397\u03a3\u039a\u0395\u03a5\u039c\u0391\u03a4\u03a9\u039d \u2013 10-03-20 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae \u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bb\u03